value.description: The value associated with this action . The value depends on the directive . If the directive is RESPONSE , then the value returned is status. haPeerId.description: The unique identifier to represent the failover peer NetScaler

haPeerIpAddress.description: This represents the ipaddress of the failover peer NetScaler(Only for HA over IPv4). For HA over IPv6 (as well as IPv4) haPeerInetAddr will contain this information.

haPeerState.name: haPeerState
haPeerState.description: This represents the state of the failover peer NetScaler whether Primary or Secondary

haTotStateTransitions.name: haTotStateTransitions
haTotStateTransitions.description: Total number of master state changes that the NetScaler appliance has made from primary to secondary and vice-versa.

haTimeofLastStateTransition.name: haTimeofLastStateTransition
haTimeofLastStateTransition.description: This represents the time since the NetScaler underwent a state change from primary to secondary or vice-versa

haTotStateFail.name: haTotStateFail
haTotStateFail.description: Number of times state changed to PARTIAL_FAIL/PARTIAL_FAIL_SSL/ROUTEMONITOR_FAIL/COMPLETE_FAIL.

haErrSyncFailure.name: haErrSyncFailure
haErrSyncFailure.description: Number of times the configuration of the primary and secondary nodes failed to synchronize since that last transition. A synchronization failure results in mismatched configuration. It can be caused by a mismatch in the Remote Procedural Call (RPC) password on the two nodes forming the high availability pair.

haErrTotNodeDown.name: haErrTotNodeDown
haErrTotNodeDown.description: Total number of heart-beats missed while the peer node was DOWN.

haErrPropMemFail.name: haErrPropMemFail
haErrPropMemFail.description: Total number of times memory allocation failed during command propagation.

haErrNsbMemFail.name: haErrNsbMemFail
haErrNsbMemFail.description: Total number of times memory allocation failed while sending heartbeats.

haErrPortSilent.name: haErrPortSilent
haErrPortSilent.description: Total number of times heartbeat packets were not received on any enabled interface for the duration of the Dead Interval.

haTotTimerRecoveries.name: haTotTimerRecoveries
haTotTimerRecoveries.description: Total number of times HA engine recovered from tight loops. (i.e., Total number of times HA timers are not called for MAX down time).

haErrSwMonitorFail.name: haErrSwMonitorFail
haErrSwMonitorFail.description: Total number of times heartbeats were not received from the peer node within the Hello Interval time.

haNicsMonitorFailed.name: haNicsMonitorFailed
haNicsMonitorFailed.description: Interfaces on which HA heartbeats are not being seen

haLastMasterStateTransitionReason.name: haLastMasterStateTransitionReason
haLastMasterStateTransitionReason.description: The reason for the last master state transition. This gives the conditions under which this node assumed the current state. The current state is available at the oid sysHighAvailabilityMode.0

haErrPropTimeout.name: haErrPropTimeout
haErrPropTimeout.description: Number of times propagation timed out.

haCurDerivedInc.name: haCurDerivedInc
haCurDerivedInc.description: Derived incarnation based on IOCTLs received.

haCurPeerInc.name: haCurPeerInc
haCurPeerInc.description: The peer's incarnation as seen from heartbeats.

haTotPktTx.name: haTotPktTx
haTotPktTx.description: Number of heartbeat packets sent to the peer node. Heartbeats are sent at regular intervals (default is 200 milliseconds) to determine the state of the peer node.

haTotPktRx.name: haTotPktRx
haTotPktRx.description: Number of heartbeat packets received from the peer node. Heartbeats are sent at regular intervals (default is 200 milliseconds) to determine the state of the peer node.

haCurStatus.name: haCurStatus
haCurStatus.description: Whether a NetScaler appliance is configured for high availability. Possible values are YES and NO. If the value is NO, the high availability statistics below are invalid.

haCurState.name: haCurState
haCurState.description: State of the HA node, based on its health, in a high availability setup. Possible values are: UP Indicates that the node is accessible and can function as either a primary or secondary node. DISABLED Indicates that the high availability status of the node has been manually disabled. Synchronization and propagation cannot take place between the peer nodes. INIT Indicates that the node is in the process of becoming part of the high availability configuration. PARTIALFAIL Indicates that one of the high availability monitored interfaces has failed because of a card or link failure. This state triggers a failover. COMPLETEFAIL Indicates that all the interfaces of the node are unusable, because the interfaces on which high availability monitoring is enabled are not connected or are manually disabled. This state triggers a failover. DUMB Indicates that the node is in listening mode. It does not participate in high availability transitions or transfer configuration from the peer node. This is a configured value, not a statistic. PARTIALFAILSSL Indicates that the SSL card has failed. This state triggers a failover. ROUTEMONITORFAIL Indicates that the route monitor has failed. This state triggers a failover.

All voltage counters stats with 'v', fan counters starts with 'fan' and temperature counters starts with 't'. Eg:'v50p' is a voltage counter that carries the value of the +5v counter.

sysHealthCounterValue.name: sysHealthCounterValue

sysHealthDiskSize.name: sysHealthDiskSize
sysHealthDiskSize.description: The total disk space in MBytes (includes available and used spaces also).

sysHealthDiskAvail.name: sysHealthDiskAvail

sysHealthDiskUsed.name: sysHealthDiskUsed

sysHealthDiskPerusage.name: sysHealthDiskPerusage
sysHealthDiskPerusage.description: The Percentage of the disk space used.

numPEs.name: numPEs
numPEs.description: The Netscaler number of PEs running

ipTotBadlens.name: ipTotBadlens
ipTotBadlens.description: Packets received with a length greater than the normal maximum transmission unit of 1514 bytes.

ipTotBadMacAddrs.name: ipTotBadMacAddrs
ipTotBadMacAddrs.description: IP packets transmitted with a bad MAC address.

ipTotMaxClients.name: ipTotMaxClients
ipTotMaxClients.description: Attempts to open a new connection to a service for which the maximum limit has been exceeded. Default value, 0, applies no limit.

ipTotUnknownSvcs.name: ipTotUnknownSvcs
ipTotUnknownSvcs.description: Packets received on a port or service that is not configured.

ipTotLandattacks.name: ipTotLandattacks
ipTotLandattacks.description: Land-attack packets received. The source and destination addresses are the same.

ipTotBadChecksums.name: ipTotBadChecksums
ipTotBadChecksums.description: Packets received with an IP checksum error.

ipTotReassemblyAttempt.name: ipTotReassemblyAttempt
ipTotReassemblyAttempt.description: IP packets that the NetScaler attempts to reassemble. If one of the fragments is missing, the whole packet is dropped.

ipTotSuccReassembly.name: ipTotSuccReassembly
ipTotSuccReassembly.description: Fragmented IP packets successfully reassembled on the NetScaler.

ipTotUnsuccReassembly.name: ipTotUnsuccReassembly
ipTotUnsuccReassembly.description: Packets received that could not be reassembled. This can occur when there is a checksum failure, an identification field mismatch, or when one of the fragments is missing.

ipTotTooBig.name: ipTotTooBig
ipTotTooBig.description: Packets received for which the reassembled data exceeds the Ethernet packet data length of 1500 bytes.

ipTotZeroFragmentLen.name: ipTotZeroFragmentLen
ipTotZeroFragmentLen.description: Packets received with a fragment length of 0 bytes.

ipTotDupFragments.name: ipTotDupFragments
ipTotDupFragments.description: Duplicate IP fragments received. This can occur when the acknowledgement was not received within the expected time.

ipTotOutOfOrderFrag.name: ipTotOutOfOrderFrag
ipTotOutOfOrderFrag.description: Fragments received that are out of order.

ipTotUnknownDstRcvd.name: ipTotUnknownDstRcvd
ipTotUnknownDstRcvd.description: Packets received in which the destination IP address was not reachable or not owned by the NetScaler.

ipTotBadTransport.name: ipTotBadTransport
ipTotBadTransport.description: Packets received in which the protocol specified in the IP header is unknown to the NetScaler.

ipTotVIPDown.name: ipTotVIPDown
ipTotVIPDown.description: Packets received for which the VIP is down. This can occur when all the services bound to the VIP are down or the VIP is manually disabled.

ipTotFixHeaderFail.name: ipTotFixHeaderFail
ipTotFixHeaderFail.description: Packets received that contain an error in one or more components of the IP header.

ipTotAddrLookup.name: ipTotAddrLookup
ipTotAddrLookup.description: IP address lookups performed by the NetScaler. When a packet is received on a non-established session, the NetScaler checks if the destination IP address is one of the NetScaler owned IP addresses.

ipTotAddrLookupFail.name: ipTotAddrLookupFail
ipTotAddrLookupFail.description: IP address lookups performed by the NetScaler that have failed because the destination IP address of the packet does not match any of the NetScaler owned IP addresses.

ipTotUDPfragmentsFwd.name: ipTotUDPfragmentsFwd
ipTotUDPfragmentsFwd.description: UDP fragments forwarded to the client or the server.

ipTotTCPfragmentsFwd.name: ipTotTCPfragmentsFwd
ipTotTCPfragmentsFwd.description: TCP fragments forwarded to the client or the server.

ipTotFragPktsGen.name: ipTotFragPktsGen
ipTotFragPktsGen.description: Fragmented packets created by the NetScaler.

ipTotInvalidHeaderSz.name: ipTotInvalidHeaderSz
ipTotInvalidHeaderSz.description: Packets received in which an invalid data length is specified, or the value in the length field and the actual data length do not match. The range for the Ethernet packet data length is 0-1500 bytes.

ipTotInvalidPacketSize.name: ipTotInvalidPacketSize
ipTotInvalidPacketSize.description: Total number of packets received by NetScaler with invalid IP packet size.

ipTotTruncatedPackets.name: ipTotTruncatedPackets
ipTotTruncatedPackets.description: Truncated IP packets received. An overflow in the routers along the path can truncate IP packets.

ipTotZeroNextHop.name: ipTotZeroNextHop
ipTotZeroNextHop.description: Packets received that contain a 0 value in the next hop field. These packets are dropped.

ipTotTtlExpired.name: ipTotTtlExpired
ipTotTtlExpired.description: Packets for which the time-to-live (TTL) expired during transit. These packets are dropped.

icmpCurRateThreshold.name: icmpCurRateThreshold
icmpCurRateThreshold.description: Limit for ICMP packets handled every 10 milliseconds. Default value, 0, applies no limit. This is a configurable value using the set rateControl command.

icmpTotRxEcho.name: icmpTotRxEcho
icmpTotRxEcho.description: ICMP Ping Echo Request and Echo Reply packets received.

icmpTotPktsDropped.name: icmpTotPktsDropped
icmpTotPktsDropped.description: ICMP packets dropped because the rate threshold has been exceeded.

icmpTotThresholdExceeds.name: icmpTotThresholdExceeds
icmpTotThresholdExceeds.description: Times the ICMP rate threshold is exceeded. If this counter continuously increases, first make sure the ICMP packets received are genuine. If they are, increase the current rate threshold.

icmpTotPortUnreachableRx.name: icmpTotPortUnreachableRx
icmpTotPortUnreachableRx.description: ICMP Port Unreachable error messages received. This error is generated when there is no service is running on the port.

icmpTotPortUnreachableTx.name: icmpTotPortUnreachableTx
icmpTotPortUnreachableTx.description: ICMP Port Unreachable error messages generated. This error is generated when there is no service is running on the port.

icmpTotBadChecksum.name: icmpTotBadChecksum
icmpTotBadChecksum.description: ICMP Fragmentation Needed error messages received with an ICMP checksum error.

icmpTotNeedFragRx.name: icmpTotNeedFragRx
icmpTotNeedFragRx.description: ICMP Fragmentation Needed error messages received for packets that need to be fragmented but for which Don't Fragment is specified the header.

icmpTotNonFirstIpFrag.name: icmpTotNonFirstIpFrag
icmpTotNonFirstIpFrag.description: ICMP Fragmentation Needed error messages received that were generated by an IP fragment other than the first one.

icmpTotInvalidBodyLen.name: icmpTotInvalidBodyLen
icmpTotInvalidBodyLen.description: ICMP Fragmentation Needed error messages received that specified an invalid body length.

icmpTotNoTcpConn.name: icmpTotNoTcpConn
icmpTotNoTcpConn.description: ICMP Need Fragmentation error messages received for TCP packets. The state of the connection for these packets is not maintained on the NetScaler.

icmpTotNoUdpConn.name: icmpTotNoUdpConn
icmpTotNoUdpConn.description: ICMP Need Fragmentation error messages received for UDP packets. The state of the connection for these packets is not maintained on the NetScaler.

icmpTotInvalidTcpSeqno.name: icmpTotInvalidTcpSeqno
icmpTotInvalidTcpSeqno.description: ICMP Fragmentation Needed error messages received for packets that contain an invalid TCP address.

icmpTotInvalidNextMTUval.name: icmpTotInvalidNextMTUval
icmpTotInvalidNextMTUval.description: ICMP Fragmentation Needed error messages received in which the Maximum Transmission Unit (MTU) for the next hop is out of range. The range for the MTU is 576-1500.

icmpTotDstIpLookup.name: icmpTotDstIpLookup
icmpTotDstIpLookup.description: Total number of MTU lookup on destination IP info received on a need fragmentation ICMP error message failed.

icmpTotBigNextMTU.name: icmpTotBigNextMTU
icmpTotBigNextMTU.description: ICMP Fragmentation Needed error messages received in which the value for the next MTU is higher than that of the current MTU.

icmpTotInvalidProtocol.name: icmpTotInvalidProtocol
icmpTotInvalidProtocol.description: ICMP Fragmentation Needed error messages received that contain a protocol other than TCP and UDP.

icmpTotBadPMTUIpChecksum.name: icmpTotBadPMTUIpChecksum
icmpTotBadPMTUIpChecksum.description: ICMP Fragmentation Needed error messages received with an IP checksum error.

icmpTotPMTUnoLink.name: icmpTotPMTUnoLink
icmpTotPMTUnoLink.description: ICMP Fragmentation Needed error messages received on a Protocol Control Block (PCB) with no link. The PCB maintains the state of the connection.

icmpTotPMTUDiscoveryDisabled.name: icmpTotPMTUDiscoveryDisabled
icmpTotPMTUDiscoveryDisabled.description: ICMP Need Fragmentation error messages received when the PMTU Discovery mode is not enabled.

udpCurRateThreshold.name: udpCurRateThreshold
udpCurRateThreshold.description: Limit for UDP packets handled every 10 milliseconds. Default value, 0, applies no limit. This is a configurable value using the set rateControl command.

udpTotUnknownSvcPkts.name: udpTotUnknownSvcPkts
udpTotUnknownSvcPkts.description: UDP packets received (but dropped) on a NetScaler port number that is not assigned to any service.

udpCurRateThresholdExceeds.name: udpCurRateThresholdExceeds
udpCurRateThresholdExceeds.description: Number of times the UDP rate threshold is exceeded. If this counter continuously increases, first make sure the UDP packets received are genuine. If they are, increase the current rate threshold.

udpBadChecksum.name: udpBadChecksum
udpBadChecksum.description: Packets received with a UDP checksum error.

tcpCurServerConn.name: tcpCurServerConn
tcpCurServerConn.description: Server connections, including connections in the Opening, Established, and Closing state.

tcpCurClientConn.name: tcpCurClientConn
tcpCurClientConn.description: Client connections, including connections in the Opening, Established, and Closing state.

tcpActiveServerConn.name: tcpActiveServerConn
tcpActiveServerConn.description: Connections to a server currently responding to requests.

tcpCurClientConnClosing.name: tcpCurClientConnClosing
tcpCurClientConnClosing.description: Client connections in the Closing state, which indicates that the connection termination process has initiated but is not complete.

tcpCurServerConnEstablished.name: tcpCurServerConnEstablished
tcpCurServerConnEstablished.description: Current server connections in the Established state, which indicates that data transfer can occur between the NetScaler and the server.

tcpCurClientConnOpening.name: tcpCurClientConnOpening
tcpCurClientConnOpening.description: Client connections in the Opening state, which indicates that the handshakes are not yet complete.

tcpCurClientConnEstablished.name: tcpCurClientConnEstablished
tcpCurClientConnEstablished.description: Current client connections in the Established state, which indicates that data transfer can occur between the NetScaler and the client.

tcpCurServerConnClosing.name: tcpCurServerConnClosing
tcpCurServerConnClosing.description: Server connections in the Closing state, which indicates that the connection termination process has initiated but is not complete.

tcpSpareConn.name: tcpSpareConn
tcpSpareConn.description: Spare connections available. To save time and resources in establishing another connection for a new client, the connection on the server is not closed after completing the request from the first client and is available for serving future requests.

tcpSurgeQueueLen.name: tcpSurgeQueueLen
tcpSurgeQueueLen.description: Connections in the surge queue. When the NetScaler cannot open a connection to the server, for example when maximum connections have been reached, the NetScaler queues these requests.

tcpCurServerConnOpening.name: tcpCurServerConnOpening
tcpCurServerConnOpening.description: Server connections in the Opening state, which indicates that the handshakes are not yet complete.

tcpTotServerConnOpened.name: tcpTotServerConnOpened
tcpTotServerConnOpened.description: Server connections initiated by the NetScaler since startup. This counter is reset when the NetScaler is restarted.

tcpTotServerConnClosed.name: tcpTotServerConnClosed
tcpTotServerConnClosed.description: Total number of closed server connections

tcpTotClientConnOpened.name: tcpTotClientConnOpened
tcpTotClientConnOpened.description: Client connections initiated on the NetScaler since startup. This counter is reset when the NetScaler is restarted.

tcpTotClientConnClosed.name: tcpTotClientConnClosed
tcpTotClientConnClosed.description: Total number of closed client connections

tcpTotSynProbe.name: tcpTotSynProbe
tcpTotSynProbe.description: Probes from the NetScaler to a server. The NetScaler sends a SYN packet to the server to check its availability and expects a SYN_ACK packet from the server before a specified response timeout.

tcpTotSvrFin.name: tcpTotSvrFin
tcpTotSvrFin.description: FIN packets received from the server.

tcpTotCltFin.name: tcpTotCltFin
tcpTotCltFin.description: FIN packets received from the clients.

tcpWaitToSyn.name: tcpWaitToSyn
tcpWaitToSyn.description: SYN packets received on connections that are in the TIME_WAIT state. Packets cannot be transferred on a connection in this state.

tcpTotZombieCltConnFlushed.name: tcpTotZombieCltConnFlushed
tcpTotZombieCltConnFlushed.description: Client connections that are flushed because the client has been idle for some time.

tcpTotZombieSvrConnFlushed.name: tcpTotZombieSvrConnFlushed
tcpTotZombieSvrConnFlushed.description: Server connections that are flushed because there have been no client requests in the queue for some time.

tcpTotZombieHalfOpenCltConnFlushed.name: tcpTotZombieHalfOpenCltConnFlushed
tcpTotZombieHalfOpenCltConnFlushed.description: Half-opened client connections that are flushed because the three-way handshakes are not complete.

tcpTotZombieHalfOpenSvrConnFlushed.name: tcpTotZombieHalfOpenSvrConnFlushed
tcpTotZombieHalfOpenSvrConnFlushed.description: Half-opened server connections that are flushed because the three-way handshakes are not complete.

tcpTotZombieActiveHalfCloseCltConnFlushe.name: tcpTotZombieActiveHalfCloseCltConnFlushed
tcpTotZombieActiveHalfCloseCltConnFlushe.description: Active half-closed client connections that are flushed because the client has closed the connection and there has been no activity on the connection.

tcpTotZombieActiveHalfCloseSvrConnFlushe.name: tcpTotZombieActiveHalfCloseSvrConnFlushed
tcpTotZombieActiveHalfCloseSvrConnFlushe.description: Active half-closed server connections that are flushed because the server has closed the connection and there has been no activity on the connection.

tcpTotZombiePassiveHalfCloseCltConnFlush.name: tcpTotZombiePassiveHalfCloseCltConnFlushed
tcpTotZombiePassiveHalfCloseCltConnFlush.description: Passive half-closed client connections that are flushed because the NetScaler has closed the connection and there has been no activity on the connection.

tcpTotZombiePassiveHalfCloseSrvConnFlush.name: tcpTotZombiePassiveHalfCloseSrvConnFlushed
tcpTotZombiePassiveHalfCloseSrvConnFlush.description: Passive half-closed server connections that are flushed because the NetScaler has closed the connection and there has been no activity on the connection.

tcpErrBadCheckSum.name: tcpErrBadCheckSum
tcpErrBadCheckSum.description: Packets received with a TCP checksum error.

tcpErrSynInSynRcvd.name: tcpErrSynInSynRcvd
tcpErrSynInSynRcvd.description: SYN packets received on a connection that is in the SYN_RCVD state. A connection goes into the SYN_RCVD state after receiving a SYN packet.

tcpErrSynInEst.name: tcpErrSynInEst
tcpErrSynInEst.description: SYN packets received on a connection that is in the ESTABLISHED state. A SYN packet is not expected on an ESTABLISHED connection.

tcpErrSynGiveUp.name: tcpErrSynGiveUp
tcpErrSynGiveUp.description: Attempts to establish a connection on the NetScaler that timed out.

tcpErrSynSentBadAck.name: tcpErrSynSentBadAck
tcpErrSynSentBadAck.description: Incorrect ACK packets received on a connection that is in the SYN_SENT state. An incorrect ACK packet is the third packet in the three-way handshake that has an incorrect sequence number.

tcpErrSynRetry.name: tcpErrSynRetry
tcpErrSynRetry.description: SYN packets resent to a server.

tcpErrFinRetry.name: tcpErrFinRetry
tcpErrFinRetry.description: FIN packets resent to a server or a client.

tcpErrFinGiveUp.name: tcpErrFinGiveUp
tcpErrFinGiveUp.description: Connections that were timed out by the NetScaler because of not receiving the ACK packet after retransmitting the FIN packet four times.

tcpErrFinDup.name: tcpErrFinDup
tcpErrFinDup.description: Number of duplicate FIN packets was recieved

tcpErrRst.name: tcpErrRst
tcpErrRst.description: Reset packets received from a client or a server.

tcpErrRstNonEst.name: tcpErrRstNonEst
tcpErrRstNonEst.description: Reset packets received on a connection that is not in the ESTABLISHED state.

tcpErrRstOutOfWindow.name: tcpErrRstOutOfWindow
tcpErrRstOutOfWindow.description: Reset packets received on a connection that is out of the current TCP window.

tcpErrRstInTimewait.name: tcpErrRstInTimewait
tcpErrRstInTimewait.description: Reset packets received on a connection that is in the TIME_WAIT state. Packets cannot be transferred on a connection in the TIME_WAIT state.

tcpErrSvrRetrasmit.name: tcpErrSvrRetrasmit
tcpErrSvrRetrasmit.description: Packets retransmitted by a server. This usually occurs because the acknowledgement from the NetScaler has not reached the server.

tcpErrCltRetrasmit.name: tcpErrCltRetrasmit
tcpErrCltRetrasmit.description: Packets retransmitted by a client. This usually occurs because the acknowledgement from the NetScaler has not reached the client.

tcpErrFullRetrasmit.name: tcpErrFullRetrasmit
tcpErrFullRetrasmit.description: Full packets retransmitted by the client or the server.

tcpErrPartialRetrasmit.name: tcpErrPartialRetrasmit
tcpErrPartialRetrasmit.description: Partial packet retransmits by a client or server due to congestion on the connection. This usually occurs because the window advertised by the NetScaler is not big enough to hold the full packet.

tcpErrSvrOutOfOrder.name: tcpErrSvrOutOfOrder
tcpErrSvrOutOfOrder.description: Out of order TCP packets received from a server.

tcpErrCltOutOfOrder.name: tcpErrCltOutOfOrder
tcpErrCltOutOfOrder.description: Out of order TCP packets received from a client.

tcpErrCltHole.name: tcpErrCltHole
tcpErrCltHole.description: TCP holes created on a client connection. When out of order packets are received from a client, a hole is created on the NetScaler for each group of missing packets.

tcpErrSvrHole.name: tcpErrSvrHole
tcpErrSvrHole.description: TCP holes created on a server connection. When out of order packets are received from a server, a hole is created on the NetScaler for each group of missing packets.

tcpErrCookiePktSeqReject.name: tcpErrCookiePktSeqReject
tcpErrCookiePktSeqReject.description: SYN cookie packets rejected because they contain an incorrect sequence number.

tcpErrCookiePktSigReject.name: tcpErrCookiePktSigReject
tcpErrCookiePktSigReject.description: SYN cookie packets rejected because they contain an incorrect signature.

tcpErrCookiePktSeqDrop.name: tcpErrCookiePktSeqDrop
tcpErrCookiePktSeqDrop.description: SYN cookie packets dropped because the sequence number specified in the packets is outside the current window.

tcpErrCookiePktMssReject.name: tcpErrCookiePktMssReject
tcpErrCookiePktMssReject.description: SYN cookie packets rejected because the maximum segment size (MSS) specified in the packets is incorrect.

tcpErrRetransmit.name: tcpErrRetransmit
tcpErrRetransmit.description: TCP packets retransmitted. The NetScaler attempts to retransmit the packet up to seven times, after which it resets the other half of the TCP connection.

tcpErrRetransmitGiveUp.name: tcpErrRetransmitGiveUp
tcpErrRetransmitGiveUp.description: Times the NetScaler terminates a connection after retransmitting the packet seven times on that connection.

pcbTotZombieCall.name: pcbTotZombieCall
pcbTotZombieCall.description: Times the Zombie cleanup function is called. Every time a connection is flushed, it is marked for cleanup. The Zombie cleanup function clears all these connections at predefined intervals.

tcpTotSynHeld.name: tcpTotSynHeld
tcpTotSynHeld.description: SYN packets held on the NetScaler that are waiting for a server connection.

tcpTotSynFlush.name: tcpTotSynFlush
tcpTotSynFlush.description: SYN packets flushed on the NetScaler because of no response from the server for three or more seconds.

tcpTotFinWaitClosed.name: tcpTotFinWaitClosed
tcpTotFinWaitClosed.description: Connections closed on the NetScaler because the number of connections in the TIME_WAIT state has exceeded the default value of 7000.

tcpErrAnyPortFail.name: tcpErrAnyPortFail
tcpErrAnyPortFail.description: Port allocations that have failed on a mapped IP address because the maximum limit of 65536 has been exceeded, or the mapped IP is not configured.

tcpErrIpPortFail.name: tcpErrIpPortFail
tcpErrIpPortFail.description: Port allocations that have failed on a subnet IP address or vserver IP address because the maximum limit of 65536 has been exceeded.

tcpErrSentRst.name: tcpErrSentRst
tcpErrSentRst.description: Reset packets sent to a client or a server.

tcpErrBadStateConn.name: tcpErrBadStateConn
tcpErrBadStateConn.description: Connections that are not in a valid TCP state.

tcpErrFastRetransmissions.name: tcpErrFastRetransmissions
tcpErrFastRetransmissions.description: TCP packets on which the NetScaler performs a fast retransmission in response to three duplicate acknowledgements or a partial acknowledgement. The NetScaler assumes that the packet is lost and retransmits the packet before its time-out.

tcpErrFirstRetransmissions.name: tcpErrFirstRetransmissions
tcpErrFirstRetransmissions.description: Packets retransmitted once by the NetScaler.

tcpErrSecondRetransmissions.name: tcpErrSecondRetransmissions
tcpErrSecondRetransmissions.description: Packets retransmitted twice by the NetScaler.

tcpErrThirdRetransmissions.name: tcpErrThirdRetransmissions
tcpErrThirdRetransmissions.description: Packets retransmitted three times by the NetScaler.

tcpErrForthRetransmissions.name: tcpErrForthRetransmissions
tcpErrForthRetransmissions.description: Packets retransmitted four times by the NetScaler.

tcpErrFifthRetransmissions.name: tcpErrFifthRetransmissions
tcpErrFifthRetransmissions.description: Packets retransmitted five times by the NetScaler.

tcpErrSixthRetransmissions.name: tcpErrSixthRetransmissions
tcpErrSixthRetransmissions.description: Packets retransmitted six times by the NetScaler.

tcpErrSeventhRetransmissions.name: tcpErrSeventhRetransmissions
tcpErrSeventhRetransmissions.description: Packets retransmitted seven times by the NetScaler. If this fails, the NetScaler terminates the connection.

tcpErrDataAfterFin.name: tcpErrDataAfterFin
tcpErrDataAfterFin.description: Bytes received following a connection termination request. This error is usually caused by a reordering of packets during transmission.

tcpErrRstThreshold.name: tcpErrRstThreshold
tcpErrRstThreshold.description: Reset packets dropped because the default threshold of 100 resets per 10 milliseconds has been exceeded. This is a configurable value using the set rateControl command.

tcpErrOutOfWindowPkts.name: tcpErrOutOfWindowPkts
tcpErrOutOfWindowPkts.description: Packets received that are out of the current advertised window.

tcpErrSynDroppedCongestion.name: tcpErrSynDroppedCongestion
tcpErrSynDroppedCongestion.description: SYN packets dropped because of network congestion.

tcpCurPhysicalServers.name: tcpCurPhysicalServers
tcpCurPhysicalServers.description: The number of physical servers that Netscaler has open connections with.

tcpReuseHit.name: tcpReuseHit
tcpReuseHit.description: Total no of client transactions found the server connection in the reuse-pool.

tcpWaitToData.name: tcpWaitToData
tcpWaitToData.description: Bytes of data received on connections that are in the TIME_WAIT state. Data cannot be transferred on a connection that is in this state.

tcpErrStrayPkt.name: tcpErrStrayPkt
tcpErrStrayPkt.description: Packets received on a connection whose state is not maintained on the NetScaler.

tcpTotClientConnOpenRate.name: tcpTotClientConnOpenRate
tcpTotClientConnOpenRate.description: Rate at which connections are opened in the system.

sslEngineStatus.name: sslEngineStatus
sslEngineStatus.description: State of the SSL Engine (1=UP/0=DOWN). This state is decided based on SSL Feature/License status and minimum number of cards UP.

sslSessionsPerSec.name: sslSessionsPerSec
sslSessionsPerSec.description: SSL sessions per second between client and NetScaler appliance.

sslTotTransactions.description: Number of SSL transactions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotSSLv2Transactions.name: sslTotSSLv2Transactions
sslTotSSLv2Transactions.description: Number of SSLv2 transactions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotSSLv3Transactions.name: sslTotSSLv3Transactions
sslTotSSLv3Transactions.description: Total number of SSLv3 transactions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotTLSv1Transactions.name: sslTotTLSv1Transactions
sslTotTLSv1Transactions.description: Number of TLSv1 transactions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotSessions.description: Number of SSL sessions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotSSLv2Sessions.name: sslTotSSLv2Sessions
sslTotSSLv2Sessions.description: Number of SSLv2 sessions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotSSLv3Sessions.description: Number of SSLv3 sessions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotTLSv1Sessions.name: sslTotTLSv1Sessions
sslTotTLSv1Sessions.description: Number of TLSv1 sessions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotExpiredSessions.name: sslTotExpiredSessions
sslTotExpiredSessions.description: Total number of expired SSL sessions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotNewSessions.name: sslTotNewSessions
sslTotNewSessions.description: Number of new SSL sessions created on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotSessionHits.description: Number of SSL session reuse hits on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotSessionMiss.name: sslTotSessionMiss
sslTotSessionMiss.description: Number of SSL session reuse misses on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotRenegSessions.description: Number of SSL session renegotiations on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotSSLv3RenegSessions.description: Number of session renegotiations done on SSLv3.

sslTotTLSv1RenegSessions.name: sslTotTLSv1RenegSessions
sslTotTLSv1RenegSessions.description: Number of SSL session renegotiations done on TLSv1.

sslTotSSLv2Handshakes.description: Number of handshakes on SSLv2 on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotSSLv3Handshakes.description: Number of handshakes on SSLv3 on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotTLSv1Handshakes.description: Number of SSL handshakes on TLSv1 on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotSSLv2ClientAuthentications.description: Number of client authentications done on SSLv2.

sslTotSSLv3ClientAuthentications.description: Number of client authentications done on SSLv3.

sslTotTLSv1ClientAuthentications.description: Number of client authentications done on TLSv1.

sslTotRSA512keyExchanges.description: Number of RSA 512-bit key exchanges on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotRSA1024keyExchanges.description: Number of RSA 1024-bit key exchanges on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotRSA2048keyExchanges.description: Number of RSA 2048-bit key exchanges on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotDH512keyExchanges.description: Number of Diffie-Helman 512-bit key exchanges on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotDH1024keyExchanges.description: Number of Diffie-Helman 1024-bit key exchanges on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotDH2048keyExchanges.description: Number of Diffie-Helman 2048-bit key exchanges on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotRSAAuthorizations.description: Number of RSA authentications on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotDHAuthorizations.description: Number of Diffie-Helman authentications on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTot40BitRC4Ciphers.description: Number of RC4 40-bit cipher encryptions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTot128BitRC4Ciphers.description: Number of RC4 128-bit cipher encryptions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTot40BitDESCiphers.description: Number of DES 40-bit cipher encryptions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTot56BitDESCiphers.description: Number of DES 56-bit cipher encryptions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTot168Bit3DESCiphers.description: Number of DES 168-bit cipher encryptions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTot40BitRC2Ciphers.description: Number of RC2 40-bit cipher encryptions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTot56BitRC2Ciphers.description: Number of RC2 56-bit cipher encryptions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTot128BitIDEACiphers.description: Number of IDEA 128-bit cipher encryptions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotNULLCiphers.description: Number of Null cipher encryptions on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotMD5Mac.description: Number of MD5 hashes on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotSHAMac.description: Number of SHA hashes on the NetScaler appliance.

sslTotOffloadSignRSA.description: Number of RSA sign operations offloaded to the cryptography card.

sslBeMaxMultiplexedSessions.description: Number of back-end SSL sessions reused on the NetScaler appliance.

httpTotGets.name: httpTotGets
httpTotGets.description: HTTP requests received using the GET method.

httpTotPosts.name: httpTotPosts
httpTotPosts.description: HTTP requests received using the POST method.

httpTotOthers.name: httpTotOthers
httpTotOthers.description: HTTP requests received using methods other than GET and POST. Some of the other well-defined HTTP methods are HEAD, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS, and TRACE. User-defined methods are also allowed.

httpTotResponses.name: httpTotResponses
httpTotResponses.description: HTTP responses sent including HTTP/1.0 and HTTP/1.1 responses.

httpTotClenResponses.name: httpTotClenResponses
httpTotClenResponses.description: HTTP responses sent in which the Content-length field of the HTTP header has been set. Content-length specifies the length of the content, in bytes, in the associated HTTP body.

httpTotChunkedResponses.name: httpTotChunkedResponses
httpTotChunkedResponses.description: HTTP responses sent in which the Transfer-Encoding field of the HTTP header has been set to chunked. This setting is used when the server wants to start sending the response before knowing its total length. The server breaks the response into chunks and sends them in sequence, inserting the length of each chunk before the actual data. The message ends with a chunk of size zero.

httpErrIncompleteRequests.name: httpErrIncompleteRequests
httpErrIncompleteRequests.description: HTTP requests received in which the header spans more than one packet.

httpErrIncompleteResponses.name: httpErrIncompleteResponses
httpErrIncompleteResponses.description: HTTP responses received in which the header spans more than one packet.

httpErrIncompleteHeaders.name: httpErrIncompleteHeaders
httpErrIncompleteHeaders.description: HTTP requests and responses received in which the HTTP header spans more than one packet.

httpErrServerBusy.name: httpErrServerBusy
httpErrServerBusy.description: Error responses received. Some of the error responses are: 500 Internal Server Error 501 Not Implemented 502 Bad Gateway 503 Service Unavailable 504 Gateway Timeout 505 HTTP Version Not Supported

httpTotChunkedRequests.name: httpTotChunkedRequests
httpTotChunkedRequests.description: HTTP requests in which the Transfer-Encoding field of the HTTP header has been set to chunked.

httpTotClenRequests.name: httpTotClenRequests
httpTotClenRequests.description: HTTP requests in which the Content-length field of the HTTP header has been set. Content-length specifies the length of the content, in bytes, in the associated HTTP body.

httpErrLargeContent.name: httpErrLargeContent
httpErrLargeContent.description: Large or invalid requests and responses received.

httpErrLargeCtlen.name: httpErrLargeCtlen
httpErrLargeCtlen.description: Large or invalid requests received in which the Content-length field of the HTTP header has been set. Content-length specifies the length of the content, in bytes, in the associated HTTP body.

httpErrLargeChunk.name: httpErrLargeChunk
httpErrLargeChunk.description: Large or invalid requests received in which the Transfer-Encoding field of the HTTP header has been set to chunked.

httpTotRequests.name: httpTotRequests
httpTotRequests.description: HTTP requests received, including HTTP/1.0 and HTTP/1.1 requests.

httpTotNoClenChunkResponses.name: httpTotNoClenChunkResponses
httpTotNoClenChunkResponses.description: FIN-terminated responses sent. In FIN-terminated responses, the server finishes sending the data and closes the connection.

httpErrNoreuseMultipart.name: httpErrNoreuseMultipart
httpErrNoreuseMultipart.description: HTTP multi-part responses sent. In multi-part responses, one or more entities are encapsulated within the body of a single message.

cacheMaxMemoryKB.name: cacheMaxMemoryKB
cacheMaxMemoryKB.description: Largest amount of memory the NetScaler can dedicate to caching, up to 50% of available memory. A 0 value disables caching, but the caching module continues to run.

cacheUtilizedMemoryKB.name: cacheUtilizedMemoryKB
cacheUtilizedMemoryKB.description: Amount of memory the integrated cache is currently using.

cacheNumCached.name: cacheNumCached
cacheNumCached.description: Responses currently in integrated cache. Includes responses fully downloaded, in the process of being downloaded, and expired or flushed but not yet removed.

cachePercentHit.name: cachePercentHit
cachePercentHit.description: Cache hits as percentage of the total number of requests

cacheRecentPercentHit.name: cacheRecentPercentHit
cacheRecentPercentHit.description: Recently recorded cache hit ratio expressed as percentage

cacheCurHits.name: cacheCurHits
cacheCurHits.description: This number should be close to the number of hits being served currently.

cacheCurMisses.name: cacheCurMisses
cacheCurMisses.description: Responses fetched from the origin and served from the cache. Should approximate storable misses. Does not include non-storable misses.

cachePercent304Hits.name: cachePercent304Hits
cachePercent304Hits.description: 304 responses as a percentage of all responses that the NetScaler served.

cacheRecentPercent304Hits.name: cacheRecentPercent304Hits
cacheRecentPercent304Hits.description: Recently recorded ratio of 304 hits to all hits expressed as percentage

cachePercentStoreAbleMiss.name: cachePercentStoreAbleMiss
cachePercentStoreAbleMiss.description: Responses that were fetched from the origin, stored in the cache, and then served to the client, as a percentage of all cache misses.

cacheRecentPercentStoreAbleMiss.name: cacheRecentPercentStoreAbleMiss
cacheRecentPercentStoreAbleMiss.description: Recently recorded ratio of store-able misses to all misses expressed as percentage.

cachePercentSuccessfulRevalidation.name: cachePercentSuccessfulRevalidation
cachePercentSuccessfulRevalidation.description: Percentage of times stored content was successfully revalidated by a 304 (Object Not Modifed) response rather than by a full response

cacheRecentPercentSuccessfulRevalidation.name: cacheRecentPercentSuccessfulRevalidation
cacheRecentPercentSuccessfulRevalidation.description: Recently recorded percentage of times stored content was successfully revalidated by a 304 response rather than by a full response

cachePercentByteHit.name: cachePercentByteHit
cachePercentByteHit.description: Bytes served from the cache divided by total bytes served to the client. If compression is On in the NetScaler, this ratio may not reflect the bytes served by the compression module. If the compression is Off, this ratio is the same as cachePercentOriginBandwidthSaved.

cacheRecentPercentByteHit.name: cacheRecentPercentByteHit
cacheRecentPercentByteHit.description: Recently recorded cache byte hit ratio expressed as percentage. Here we define byte hit ratio as ((number of bytes served from the cache)/(total number of bytes served to the client)). This is the standard definition of Byte Hit Ratio. If compression is turned ON in NS then this ratio doesn't mean much. This might under or over estimate the origin-to-cache bandwidth saving (depending upon whether bytes served by CMP in NetScaler are more or less than compressed bytes served from the cache). If CMP is turned OFF in NS then this ratio is same as cacheRecentPercentOriginBandwidthSaved.

cachePercentOriginBandwidthSaved.name: cachePercentOriginBandwidthSaved
cachePercentOriginBandwidthSaved.description: Percentage of origin bandwidth saved, expressed as number of bytes served from the integrated cache divided by all bytes served. The assumption is that all compression is done in the NetScaler.

cacheRecentPercentOriginBandwidthSaved.name: cacheRecentPercentOriginBandwidthSaved
cacheRecentPercentOriginBandwidthSaved.description: Bytes served from cache divided by total bytes served to client. This ratio can be greater than 1 because of the assumption that all compression has been done in the NetScaler.

cacheErrMemAlloc.name: cacheErrMemAlloc
cacheErrMemAlloc.description: Total number of times the cache failed to allocate memory to store responses.

cacheTotRequests.name: cacheTotRequests
cacheTotRequests.description: Total cache hits plus total cache misses.

cacheTotHits.name: cacheTotHits
cacheTotHits.description: Responses served from the integrated cache. These responses match a policy with a CACHE action.

cacheTotMisses.name: cacheTotMisses
cacheTotMisses.description: Intercepted HTTP requests requiring fetches from origin server.

cacheTot304Hits.name: cacheTot304Hits
cacheTot304Hits.description: Object not modified responses served from the cache. (Status code 304 served instead of the full response.)

cacheTotNon304Hits.name: cacheTotNon304Hits
cacheTotNon304Hits.description: Total number of full (non-304) responses served from the cache. A 304 status code indicates that a response has not been modified since the last time it was served

cacheTotStoreAbleMisses.name: cacheTotStoreAbleMisses
cacheTotStoreAbleMisses.description: Cache misses for which the fetched response is stored in the cache before serving it to the client. Storable misses conform to a built-in or user-defined caching policy that contains a CACHE action.

cacheTotNonStoreAbleMisses.name: cacheTotNonStoreAbleMisses
cacheTotNonStoreAbleMisses.description: Cache misses for which the fetched response is not stored in the cache. These responses match policies with a NOCACHE action or are affected by Poll Every Time.

cacheTotRevalidationMiss.name: cacheTotRevalidationMiss
cacheTotRevalidationMiss.description: Responses that an intervening cache revalidated with the integrated cache before serving, as determined by a Cache-Control: Max-Age header configurable in the integrated cache

cacheTotFullToConditionalRequest.name: cacheTotFullToConditionalRequest
cacheTotFullToConditionalRequest.description: Number of user-agent requests for a cached Poll Every Time (PET) response that were sent to the origin server as conditional requests.

cacheTotSuccessfulRevalidation.name: cacheTotSuccessfulRevalidation
cacheTotSuccessfulRevalidation.description: Total number of times stored content was successfully revalidated by a 304 Not Modified response from the origin.

cacheTotResponseBytes.name: cacheTotResponseBytes
cacheTotResponseBytes.description: Total number of HTTP response bytes served by NetScaler from both the origin and the cache

cacheBytesServed.name: cacheBytesServed
cacheBytesServed.description: Total number of bytes served from the integrated cache

cacheCompressedBytesServed.name: cacheCompressedBytesServed
cacheCompressedBytesServed.description: Number of compressed bytes served from the cache

cacheTotPetRequests.name: cacheTotPetRequests
cacheTotPetRequests.description: Requests that triggered a search of a content group that has Poll Every Time (PET) enabled (always consult the origin server before serving cached data).

cacheTotPetHits.name: cacheTotPetHits
cacheTotPetHits.description: Number of times a cache hit was found during a search of a content group that has Poll Every Time enabled.

cachePercentPetHits.name: cachePercentPetHits
cachePercentPetHits.description: Percentage of cache hits in content groups that have Poll Every Time enabled, relative to all searches of content groups with Poll Every Time enabled.

cacheTotParameterizedRequests.name: cacheTotParameterizedRequests
cacheTotParameterizedRequests.description: Total number of requests where the content group has hit and invalidation parameters or selectors.

cacheTotParameterizedHits.name: cacheTotParameterizedHits
cacheTotParameterizedHits.description: Parameterized requests resulting in either a 304 or non-304 hit.

cacheTotParameterizedNon304Hits.name: cacheTotParameterizedNon304Hits
cacheTotParameterizedNon304Hits.description: Parameterized requests resulting in a full response (not status code 304: Object Not Updated) served from the cache.

cacheTotParameterized304Hits.name: cacheTotParameterized304Hits
cacheTotParameterized304Hits.description: Parameterized requests resulting in an object not modified (status code 304) response.

cachePercentParameterized304Hits.name: cachePercentParameterized304Hits
cachePercentParameterized304Hits.description: Percentage of parameterized 304 hits relative to all parameterized hits.

cacheRecentPercentParameterizedHits.name: cacheRecentPercentParameterizedHits
cacheRecentPercentParameterizedHits.description: Recently recorded ratio of parameterized 304 hits to all parameterized hits expressed as a percentage

cacheTotInvalidationRequests.name: cacheTotInvalidationRequests
cacheTotInvalidationRequests.description: Requests that match an invalidation policy and result in expiration of specific cached responses or entire content groups.

cacheTotNonParameterizedInvalidationRequ.name: cacheTotNonParameterizedInvalidationRequests
cacheTotNonParameterizedInvalidationRequ.description: Requests that match an invalidation policy where the invalGroups parameter is configured and expires one or more content groups.

cacheTotParameterizedInvalidationRequest.name: cacheTotParameterizedInvalidationRequests
cacheTotParameterizedInvalidationRequest.description: Requests matching a policy with an invalidation (INVAL) action and a content group that uses an invalidation selector or parameters.

cacheLargestResponseReceived.name: cacheLargestResponseReceived
cacheLargestResponseReceived.description: Size, in bytes, of largest response sent to client from the cache or the origin server.

cacheTotFlashcacheMisses.name: cacheTotFlashcacheMisses
cacheTotFlashcacheMisses.description: Number of requests to a content group with flash cache enabled that were cache misses. Flash cache distributes the response to all the clients in aqueue.

cacheTotFlashcacheHits.name: cacheTotFlashcacheHits
cacheTotFlashcacheHits.description: Number of requests to a content group with flash cache enabled that were cache hits. The flash cache setting queues requests that arrive simultaneously and distributes the response to all the clients in the queue.

cacheTotExpireAtLastByte.name: cacheTotExpireAtLastByte
cacheTotExpireAtLastByte.description: Instances of content expiring immediately after receiving the last body byte due to the Expire at Last Byte setting for the content group.

cacheNumMarker.name: cacheNumMarker
cacheNumMarker.description: Marker objects created when a response exceeds the maximum or minimum size for entries in its content group or has not yet received the minimum number of hits required for items in its content group.

cacheMaxMemoryActiveKB.name: cacheMaxMemoryActiveKB
cacheMaxMemoryActiveKB.description: Currently active value of maximum memory

cache64MaxMemoryKB.name: cache64MaxMemoryKB
cache64MaxMemoryKB.description: Largest amount of memory the NetScaler can dedicate to caching, up to 50% of available memory. A 0 value disables caching, but the caching module continues to run.

compTotalRequests.name: compTotalRequests
compTotalRequests.description: Number of HTTP compression requests the NetScaler receives for which the response is successfully compressed. For example, after you enable compression and configure services, if you send requests to the NetScaler with the following header information: Accept-Encoding: gzip, deflate, and NetScaler compresses the corresponding response, this counter is incremented.

compTotalTxBytes.name: compTotalTxBytes
compTotalTxBytes.description: Number of bytes the NetScaler sends to the client after compressing the response from the server.

compTotalRxBytes.name: compTotalRxBytes
compTotalRxBytes.description: Number of bytes that can be compressed, which the NetScaler receives from the server. This gives the content length of the response that the NetScaler receives from server.

compTotalTxPackets.name: compTotalTxPackets
compTotalTxPackets.description: Number of HTTP packets that the NetScaler sends to the client after compressing the response from the server.

compTotalRxPackets.name: compTotalRxPackets
compTotalRxPackets.description: Number of HTTP packets that can be compressed, which the NetScaler receives from the server.

compRatio.name: compRatio
compRatio.description: Ratio of compressible data received to compressed data transmitted expressed as percentage.

compTotalDataCompressionRatio.name: compTotalDataCompressionRatio
compTotalDataCompressionRatio.description: Ratio of total HTTP data received to total HTTP data transmitted expressed as percentage.

compTcpTotalTxBytes.name: compTcpTotalTxBytes
compTcpTotalTxBytes.description: Number of bytes that the NetScaler sends to the client after compressing the response from the server.

compTcpTotalRxBytes.name: compTcpTotalRxBytes
compTcpTotalRxBytes.description: Number of bytes that can be compressed, which the NetScaler receives from the server. This gives the content length of the response that the NetScaler receives from server.

compTcpTotalTxPackets.name: compTcpTotalTxPackets
compTcpTotalTxPackets.description: Number of TCP packets that the NetScaler sends to the client after compressing the response from the server.

compTcpTotalRxPackets.name: compTcpTotalRxPackets
compTcpTotalRxPackets.description: Total number of compressible packets received by NetScaler.

compTcpTotalQuantum.name: compTcpTotalQuantum
compTcpTotalQuantum.description: Number of times the NetScaler compresses a quantum of data. NetScaler buffers the data received from the server till it reaches the quantum size and then compresses the buffered data and transmits to the client.

compTcpTotalPush.name: compTcpTotalPush
compTcpTotalPush.description: Number of times the NetScaler compresses data on receiving a TCP PUSH flag from the server. The PUSH flag ensures that data is compressed immediately without waiting for the buffered data size to reach the quantum size.

compTcpTotalEoi.name: compTcpTotalEoi
compTcpTotalEoi.description: Number of times the NetScaler compresses data on receiving End Of Input (FIN packet). When the NetScaler receives End Of Input (FIN packet), it compresses the buffered data immediately without waiting for the buffered data size to reach the quantum size.

compTcpTotalTimer.name: compTcpTotalTimer
compTcpTotalTimer.description: Number of times the NetScaler compresses data on expiration of data accumulation timer. The timer expires if the server response is very slow and consequently, the NetScaler does not receive response for a certain amount of time. Under such a condition, the NetScaler compresses the buffered data immediately without waiting for the buffered data size to reach the quantum size.

compTcpRatio.name: compTcpRatio
compTcpRatio.description: Ratio of compressible data received to compressed data transmitted expressed as percentage.

compTcpBandwidthSaving.name: compTcpBandwidthSaving
compTcpBandwidthSaving.description: Bandwidth saving from TCP compression expressed as percentage.

deCompTcpRxPackets.name: deCompTcpRxPackets
deCompTcpRxPackets.description: Total number of compressed packets received by NetScaler.

deCompTcpTxPackets.name: deCompTcpTxPackets
deCompTcpTxPackets.description: Total number of decompressed packets transmitted by NetScaler.

deCompTcpRxBytes.name: deCompTcpRxBytes
deCompTcpRxBytes.description: Total number of compressed bytes received by NetScaler.

deCompTcpTxBytes.name: deCompTcpTxBytes
deCompTcpTxBytes.description: Total number of decompressed bytes transmitted by NetScaler.

deCompTcpErrData.name: deCompTcpErrData
deCompTcpErrData.description: Number of data errors encountered while decompressing.

deCompTcpErrLessData.name: deCompTcpErrLessData
deCompTcpErrLessData.description: Number of times NetScaler received less data than declared by protocol.

deCompTcpErrMoreData.name: deCompTcpErrMoreData
deCompTcpErrMoreData.description: Number of times NetScaler received more data than declared by protocol.

deCompTcpErrMemory.name: deCompTcpErrMemory
deCompTcpErrMemory.description: Number of times memory failures occurred while decompressing.

deCompTcpErrUnknown.name: deCompTcpErrUnknown
deCompTcpErrUnknown.description: Number of times unknown errors occurred while decompressing.

deCompTcpRatio.name: deCompTcpRatio
deCompTcpRatio.description: Ratio of decompressed data transmitted to compressed data received expressed as percentage.

deCompTcpBandwidthSaving.name: deCompTcpBandwidthSaving
deCompTcpBandwidthSaving.description: Bandwidth saving from compression expressed as percentage.

delCompTotalRequests.name: delCompTotalRequests
delCompTotalRequests.description: Total number of delta compression requests received by NetScaler.

delCompFirstAccess.name: delCompFirstAccess
delCompFirstAccess.description: Total number of delta compression first accesses.

delCompDone.name: delCompDone
delCompDone.description: Total number of delta compressions done by NetScaler.

delCompTcpRxBytes.name: delCompTcpRxBytes
delCompTcpRxBytes.description: Total number of delta-compressible bytes received by NetScaler.

delCompTcpTxBytes.name: delCompTcpTxBytes
delCompTcpTxBytes.description: Total number of delta-compressed bytes transmitted by NetScaler.

delCompTcpTxPackets.name: delCompTcpTxPackets
delCompTcpTxPackets.description: Total number of delta-compressed packets transmitted by NetScaler.

delCompBaseServed.name: delCompBaseServed
delCompBaseServed.description: Total number of basefile requests served by NetScaler.

delCompBaseTcpTxBytes.name: delCompBaseTcpTxBytes
delCompBaseTcpTxBytes.description: Number of basefile bytes transmitted by NetScaler.

delCompErrBypassed.name: delCompErrBypassed
delCompErrBypassed.description: Number of times delta-compression bypassed by NetScaler.

delCompErrBFileWHdrFailed.name: delCompErrBFileWHdrFailed
delCompErrBFileWHdrFailed.description: Number of times basefile could not be updated in NetScaler cache.

delCompErrNostoreMiss.name: delCompErrNostoreMiss
delCompErrNostoreMiss.description: Number of times basefile was not found in NetScaler cache.

delCompErrReqinfoToobig.name: delCompErrReqinfoToobig
delCompErrReqinfoToobig.description: Number of times basefile request URL was too large.

delCompErrReqinfoAllocfail.name: delCompErrReqinfoAllocfail
delCompErrReqinfoAllocfail.description: Number of times requested basefile could not be allocated.

delCompErrSessallocFail.name: delCompErrSessallocFail
delCompErrSessallocFail.description: Number of times delta compression session could not be allocated.

delCmpRatio.name: delCmpRatio

ifErrDroppedRxPkts.name: ifErrDroppedRxPkts
ifErrDroppedRxPkts.description: Number of packets dropped by the specified interface. Commonly dropped packets are multicast frames, spanning tree BPDUs, packets destined to a MAC not owned by the system when L2 mode is disabled, or packets tagged for a vlan that isnt bound to the interface. This counter will increment in most healthy networks at a steady rate regardless of traffic load. If a sharp spike in dropped packets occurs, it generally indicates an issue with connected L2 switches, such as a forwarding database overflow resulting in packets being broadcast on all ports.

ifLinkReinits.name: ifLinkReinits

ifnicTxStalls.name: ifnicTxStalls

ifnicRxStalls.name: ifnicRxStalls
ifnicRxStalls.description: Number of system registered stalls in the reception of packets on the specified interface. When the link is up for more than 10 minutes and packets have been transmitted, but no packets have been received for 16 seconds, the network interface card is said to be in a receive stall state. This commonly occurs in lab environments when no packets, including spanning tree, are being received on the wire.
